Process called "parse_proc_call_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The `proc` keyword introduces a NAMED function call, optionally qualified by
    the defining module: `proc func [.field | from Module] [with arg, ...]`. This
    is the dominant cross-module call surface in the self-hosting compiler source
    (e.g. `proc allocate from Layout`, `proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with t,
    0`). It is NOT an indirect call through a function-pointer variable -- the
    monolith stage1 (parser.runa::parser_parse_proc_expression) reads the callee
    as a bare NAME token and always emits a direct function call, never an
    indirect dispatch. Replicating that here is required for self-host: the
    previous implementation parsed the callee as a primary expression, never
    consumed the `from Module` qualifier, and built an AST_INDIRECT_CALL node.
    That left the `from Module ...` tail unparsed, so the whole enclosing Process
    failed to parse and was dropped; and even the unqualified `proc f with a` form
    lowered to an indirect node that produced no call instruction at all.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Consume the `proc` keyword.
    2. Read the function-NAME token's value (any token type may name a function;
       keyword/type tokens carry their lexeme as the value), then consume it.
    3. Optional dot qualifier `proc Module.func`: when the next token is TOKEN_DOT,
       the first name was the module alias -- consume the dot and read the real
       function-name token as the callee name.
    4. Optional `from Module` qualifier: when the next token is TOKEN_FROM, consume
       it and the following module-name token. Module qualifiers are source-level
       only; the import system flattens every imported function into the program
       table under its PLAIN name, so resolution (and the emitted symbol) keys off
       the plain function name exactly as the monolith's EXPR_QUALIFIED_CALL codegen
       resolves by offset-16 plain name. The module token is therefore consumed but
       does not change the callee symbol.
    5. Optional `with` argument clause: parse the canonical comma/and-separated
       argument sequence into a List, reusing parse_with_single_argument so each
       argument parses at the with-argument precedence floor (trailing comparisons
       and logical operators bind to the whole call, not the last argument).
    6. Build a plain AST_CALL_EXPRESSION whose callee is a fresh identifier node
       carrying the plain function name -- the same node shape the canonical
       `callee with args` and paren-call forms produce, so it shares the existing
       direct-call HIR lowering and emits `callq <func>`.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    A handful of token reads/consumes plus one List allocation and a linear
    argument scan. Cold relative to the per-token Pratt loop.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Every name token's value is read defensively; a null callee name aborts the
    parse (returns 0) rather than fabricating an unnamed call. A null argument
    parse aborts the whole call so no partially built node with dangling arguments
    escapes.
    @End Security_Scope

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Capture the call position from the 'proc' keyword token.
    Let proc_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let line be proc token_get_line from Parser with proc_token
    Let column be proc token_get_column from Parser with proc_token

    Note: 1. Expect and consume 'proc' keyword.
    Let result be proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_PROC
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: 2. Read the function-name token (any token type may name a function;
    Note: keyword/type tokens carry their lexeme as the value), then consume it.
    Let name_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    If name_token is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected function name after 'proc' keyword", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If
    Let func_name be proc token_get_value from Parser with name_token
    Let name_line be proc token_get_line from Parser with name_token
    Let name_column be proc token_get_column from Parser with name_token
    proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

    Note: module_alias holds the source-level module qualifier (the alias bound by
    Note: an Import statement) when the call is written `proc Module.func ...` or
    Note: `proc func from Module ...`, otherwise 0. It is the token VALUE pointer as
    Note: read from the qualifier token (lexer-owned, NUL-terminated). Stage 3 of the
    Note: separate-compilation port consumes it during AST-level mangle-resolution to
    Note: disambiguate same-named functions across modules; this stage only captures
    Note: it onto the callee node's metadata slot and adds no downstream reader, so
    Note: behavior is unchanged for every existing call form.
    Let module_alias be 0

    Note: 3. Optional dot qualifier: `proc Module.func`. The first name was the
    Note: module alias; the real callee name follows the dot.
    Let qual_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let qual_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with qual_token
    If qual_type is equal to TOKEN_DOT:
        Note: The name already read into func_name was the module alias; record it
        Note: before the real callee name overwrites func_name below.
        Set module_alias to func_name
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        Let dot_name_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        If dot_name_token is equal to 0:
            proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected function name after '.' in qualified proc call", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
            Return 0
        End If
        Set func_name to proc token_get_value from Parser with dot_name_token
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
    End If

    Note: 4. Optional `from Module` qualifier. The module name is source-level only
    Note: at the call site; imported functions are flattened under their plain name,
    Note: so the module token does not change the callee symbol. The alias is still
    Note: captured into module_alias for the Stage 3 mangle-resolution pass.
    Set qual_token to proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Set qual_type to proc token_get_type from Parser with qual_token
    If qual_type is equal to TOKEN_FROM:
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        Let module_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        If module_token is equal to 0:
            proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected module name after 'from' in qualified proc call", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
            Return 0
        End If
        Set module_alias to proc token_get_value from Parser with module_token
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
    End If

    If func_name is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Missing function name in proc call", name_line, name_column
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build the callee identifier carrying the plain function name.
    Let callee be proc build_identifier_node from ASTBuilder with func_name, name_line, name_column
    If callee is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Failed to create proc-call callee identifier AST node", name_line, name_column
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Stash the source-level module alias on the callee identifier node's
    Note: metadata slot (ASTNode.metadata, offset 56) so the Stage 3 AST-level
    Note: mangle-resolution pass can later distinguish same-named functions across
    Note: modules. An OWNED duplicate is stored (not the lexer-owned token value)
    Note: because destroy_ast_node deallocates whatever the metadata slot holds; a
    Note: duplicate keeps that free correct and avoids aliasing the lexer's lexeme.
    Note: When the call carries no qualifier the slot stays 0 (its create_node
    Note: default), so unqualified calls are byte-for-byte unchanged. No downstream
    Note: reader exists yet, so this capture is inert at this stage.
    If module_alias is not equal to 0:
        Let owned_alias be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with module_alias
        If owned_alias is not equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_qword from Layout with callee, 56, owned_alias
        End If
    End If

    Note: Allocate the argument list (empty when there is no `with` clause).
    Let arguments be proc create from List
    If arguments is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Failed to create proc-call argument list", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If
    Let argument_count be 0

    Note: 5. Optional `with` argument clause.
    Let with_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let with_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with with_token
    If with_type is equal to TOKEN_WITH:
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

        Loop forever:
            Let arg be proc parse_with_single_argument with parser
            If arg is equal to 0:
                proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected argument expression after 'with' in proc call", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
                Return 0
            End If

            proc list_append from List with arguments, arg
            Set argument_count to argument_count plus 1

            Note: Continue on an "and" or "," separator introducing another argument.
            Let sep_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
            Let sep_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with sep_token

            If sep_type is equal to TOKEN_AND:
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
                Continue
            End If

            If sep_type is equal to TOKEN_COMMA:
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
                Continue
            End If

            Break
        End While
    End If

    Note: 6. Build the direct call node (shared AST_CALL_EXPRESSION shape).
    Let call_node be proc build_call_expression from ASTBuilder with callee, arguments, argument_count, line, column
    If call_node is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Failed to create proc-call expression AST node", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Return call_node
End Process

