Process called "parse_a_value_of_type_construction" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse the canonical struct constructor "a value of type TypeName [with field as value, ...]".

    Note: Grammar (caller has confirmed the two-token prefix article/"value"):
    Note:   a|an value of type TypeName
    Note:   a|an value of type TypeName[GenericArgs]
    Note:   a|an value of type TypeName with f1 as e1, f2 as e2, ...
    Note: The leading article ("a"/"an") is the current token on entry; this parser
    Note: consumes the article, "value", "of", "type", the type name (and any bracketed
    Note: generic arguments), and an optional "with" field-initializer clause.

    Note: The result is an AST_RECORD_LITERAL (1013) whose value field carries the type
    Note: name string and whose children are the field VALUE expressions in source order.
    Note: This reuses the existing record-literal HIR lowering (lower_record_literal),
    Note: which allocates the aggregate and stores each field value at its positional
    Note: slot; a field-less constructor lowers to a bare aggregate allocation, exactly
    Note: what the "Set obj.field to value" follow-up statements then write into.

